A jet of flames erupted from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a specific patch of the forest ablaze, then circled above, observing it for a moment. Strangely, as it had slowed down, the odd noises and cries behind him had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't let myself be abruptly lifted by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not so bad, isn't it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi; he seemed less dark than usual and had planted his claws into Thassalin's back, so deeply that he had drawn blood from the Thraki, but evidently, he didn't care. That said, Thassalin had realized he had scared his new friends and had found a clearing to land in.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SNIFFED A SMELL. I HAD TO CHECK."
"You had to drag us here with you?" Tenuk asked as he slid down Thassalin's back and along his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our big and strong fighter! How will he join us?"
"He will find a way," Nissy replied. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive anything like Kayel's cute little car either, and if he started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU drive us there. He just has this bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly laughing hilariously, and no one understood what was funny. It took him a little too long to calm down.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A TINY BICYCLE MEANT FOR CHILDREN TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE LOVED TO BE TELPATHIC. THAT WAS A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel snickered, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up and why did you fly away so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took off, and briefly disappeared before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a rare golden and white draconic creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR WAILS. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel did too, their attention drawn by a gap in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this thing opened two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, without worrying about the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk just managed to take cover, but Nyssi was pulled along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nyssi and throwing her onto his back, using his extraordinarily long and dexterous tail, before taking off. The two-winged black creature quickly gave chase.
Kayel exhaled and drew the gun he had on his back, then opened a compartment containing a belt of ammunition. He put it over his shoulder so he could access it easily, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to transform into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"You want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And so what? I have an ultra-powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to use. I just need to see it to shoot it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make some space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body expanded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted to his normal light blue Thraki form, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb on."
Having regained a more normal Thraki appearance, Tenuk now had his back covered in scale plates, but a pair of spikes had also grown on it, practical for Kayel to grip onto. Tenuk needed a little time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
I suppose this is the other scary big monster that worried Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow while trying to shoot the second creature, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk did not react. He was too focused on his flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel clumsily turned around to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was a boon for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots went through the creature's upper wings, which howled in pain and disappeared again under the trees. Kayel did not know if it was still following them, but it certainly would not be able to catch up.
Further away, Nyssi was desperately clinging on, while Thassalin flew in circles, firing bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly injured, it seemed furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs did not seem to have the intended effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw his weapon, a reliable rifle. It was certainly not designed for this kind of situation, but a volley of shots would surely at least deter the black beast, right?
